Create the Sentiment Analysis Data Assets

Follow these steps to create sentiment analysis data assets:
In Data Manager, select the Data Templates tab.
Locate the Sentiment Analysis tile, select it, and click Next.
Answer the questions in configuration wizard.
Choose the source object for sentiment analysis.
Choose a text field from the source object to run the sentiment analysis on.
Select up to 20 additional fields from the source object to add to the dataset.
Name your data app, add an optional description, and click Create.

The data asset creation process takes some time to complete. You can view your app in progress on the Auto-Installed Apps page.

You can view detailed app creation information on the App Install History page.
title: Creating Sentiment Analysis Data Assets in Salesforce
